reviewText: It's fun to watch these old early talkies. So glad that so many of them are still available. It's almost like walking into Mr. Peabody's WABAC machine and going back in time!  Love the 1930's , the cars, the clothing, the hats... Here is James Cagney and Joan Blondell's first movie, and lighting upon the screen.
A little rough and ragged around the edges, but worth watching.  Worth the price of admission to see Cagney bawling and pleading with his mother to protect her little boy'
